				\begin{document}$$\sim$$\end{document}~2.8 along the posterior–anterior direction, with an equal factor of undersampling. In-plane oversampling occurred for 30 of the 40 patients, altering their acquisition matrix to 135–153 × 569 and 119–133 × 165 for the T1-weighted and T2-weighted FLAIR images, respectively. The FOV was extended to avoid infolding artifacts from objects outside the FOV.

